---
import LandingLayout from "../../layouts/LandingLayout.astro";
---

<LandingLayout
	title="Contract"
	description="Schema-first REST for TypeScript — route, contract, OpenAPI in one glance."
	slug="contract"
>
	<main id="main" class="lp-contract">
		<section class="hero" aria-label="Hero">
			<div class="hero-grid">
				<div class="hero-copy">
					<div class="brand-mark">
						<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="" width="40" height="40">
						Routa
						<span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					</div>
					<h1 class="headline">Schema-first REST for TypeScript</h1>
					<p class="lede">
						Filesystem routes with Zod contracts — not vibes. The route file is the API surface;
						OpenAPI stays in lockstep.
					</p>
					<div class="cta-row">
						<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/">Get started</a>
						<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/Routa-ts/Routa">GitHub</a>
					</div>
					<div class="cli" data-cmd="pnpm create routa-ts@latest">
						<span>$ pnpm create routa-ts@latest</span>
						<button type="button">Copy</button>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="stack">
					<div class="flow-label">One route · one contract</div>
					<div class="code-panel">
						<div class="code-panel__bar">
							<span>src/routes/users/route.ts</span><span>filesystem</span>
						</div>
						<pre
						><code><span class="kw">export default</span> <span class="fn">defineRoute</span>({"{"}
  post: <span class="fn">createRoute</span>({"{"}
    input: {"{"} body: CreateUserSchema {"}"},
    responses: {"{"}
      success: {"{"} status: <span class="str">201</span>, schema: UserSchema {"}"},
    {"}"},
    run: <span class="kw">async</span> ({"{"} input, ctx {"}"}) =>
      users.createUser(input.body, ctx),
  {"}"}),
{"}"});</code></pre>
					</div>
					<div class="code-panel">
						<div class="code-panel__bar"><span>schemas/user.ts</span><span>zod</span></div>
						<pre><code><span class="kw">export const</span> CreateUserSchema = z.object({"{"}
  email: z.string().email(),
  name: z.string().min(<span class="str">1</span>),
{"}"});</code></pre>
					</div>
					<div class="code-panel">
						<div class="code-panel__bar"><span>openapi.yaml · emitted</span><span>peer</span></div>
						<pre><code><span class="cm"># POST /users — generated from the contract</span>
paths:
  /users:
    post:
      responses:
        <span class="str">"201"</span>:
          description: success</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="section-inner">
				<p class="section-kicker">Primitives</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">What the contract owns</h2>
				<p class="section-lede">
					Short list. Real surfaces. Built on Hono underneath — Routa owns the contract layer.
				</p>
				<ul class="pillars">
					<li>
						<strong>Filesystem routes</strong>
						<p>Folders map to URL segments. Each route.ts owns the methods for that path.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Zod I/O</strong>
						<p>Inputs and named response outcomes are schemas — typed end to end.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>OpenAPI bidirectional</strong>
						<p>Scaffold from a spec or emit from source. Drift is a check failure.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Typed middleware</strong>
						<p>Context composes through the lattice without losing types.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>CLI lifecycle</strong>
						<p>
							<code class="mono">check</code>
							→ <code class="mono">build</code> → <code class="mono">start</code> before you ship.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Hono runtime</strong>
						<p>Web Standards handlers. Routa sits on the contract boundary.</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<ul class="built-on" style="margin-top: 2rem" aria-label="Built on">
					<li>Hono</li>
					<li>Zod</li>
					<li>OpenAPI</li>
					<li>TypeScript</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="v0-note">
					<strong>v0</strong>
					— intentionally narrow. No enterprise logo wall. No cloud funnel.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="close">
			<div class="close-inner">
				<div>
					<h2>Read the contract docs</h2>
					<p>Quickstart, route anatomy, and OpenAPI workflow under /docs/.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://routa-ts.dev/docs/start/quickstart/"
						>Quickstart</a
					>
					<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/landings/">All options</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</LandingLayout>
